etailed case studies of the United States, Australia, Western Europe, and Israel. His book will be of interest to a broad audience of sociologists, political scientists, historians, legal scholars, and area specialists.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 0aEmigration and immigrationxGovernment policy. 0aEthnic groupsxGovernment policy. 0aMulticulturalism. 0aNationalism. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674274297423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780674274297/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK